fferent SPS models are\ncomparable to the IMF variations. In our analysis we assume that the variation\nin $M/L$ and color is driven by differences in age, and that other\ncontributions (e.g., metallicity evolution, dark matter) are small. These\nassumptions may be an important source of uncertainty as galaxies evolve in\nmore complex ways.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Nov 2014 21:00:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
